        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 14 at 9:14PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 914 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southeast of Broadus, moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Broadus, Biddle, Boyes, Powderville and Olive.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
